<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="5" face="Arial"><strong>Welcome
to HeliQuest</strong></font> <a  href="HelpProcedure.htm"><img src="Helpgris.JPG" align="top" width=100 border="0"></font></a></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Arial"><strong>HeliQuest</strong> calculates from an &alpha;-helix sequence its physicochemical properties and amino acid composition and uses the results to screen any databank in order to identify protein segments possessing similar features.
<br>The server is divided into 2 interconnected modules: the <a href="/cgi-bin/ComputParams.py "> sequence analysis module </a> and the <a href="/cgi-bin/SearchMotifs.py ">screening module.</a>
<br>In addition, the mutation module, (available from the sequence analysis module), allows user to mutate helices manually or automatically by genetic algorithm to create analogues with specific properties.</p>
<TABLE BORDER=0 >
<TR>
<TD><a href="/cgi-bin/ComputParams.py "><img src="Bouton-Analysis1.jpg" align="middle" border="0"></a></TD>
<TD><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Arial">This module is dedicated to characterizing helices known by the user. It determines properties as </font><font color="#FF0080" face="Arial">hydrophobicity</font><font
face="Arial">, </font><font color="#FF0080" face="Arial">hydrophobic moment</font><font face="Arial">, </font><font color="#FF0080" face="Arial">z</font><font face="Arial"> and </font><font color="#FF0080" face="Arial">amino acid composition</font><font face="Arial">.</font>
</font><br><font size="2" face="Arial"><b>Note 1: The link to the screening module is available only if user analyzes sequences with an 18 a.a. window.</b></font>
<br><font size="2" face="Arial"><b>Note 2: A sequence can be modified by the manual or GA-based mutation modules once analysed.</b></font></p></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD> </TD>
<TD> </TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD> </TD>
<TD> </TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD><a href="/cgi-bin/SearchMotifs.py"><img src="Bouton-Screening1.JPG" align="middle" border="0"></a></TD>
<TD><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Arial">This module allows user to screen large databases in order to find sequences that have the general physico-chemical features of a target sequence.</font></p></TD>
</TABLE>


